  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nFollowing up on the Zulip discussion here: https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187030-users/topic/Quarkus.203.20changing.20entity-fields.20to.20CompositeTracker.3F\r\n\r\nWhen embedding an type in an entity where the `@Embedabble` annotation has accidentally been forgotten, a weird error message is shown that gives no clue whats going on.\r\n\r\nSee attached demo\r\n[demo.zip](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/files/12454301/demo.zip)\r\n\r\nRunning this sample (Quarkus 3.2.4) with ` ./mvnw verify`  will yield the following error.\r\n\r\n` SomeQuarkusTest.test_some:15 Â» ClassCast Object of type 'class demo.Bar' can't be cast to CompositeTracker` \r\n\r\nAdding the ` @Embedabble` to class ` Bar` and running the test again completes successfully.\r\n\r\nNote: running the \"wrong\" demo with Quarkus 2.x works without error.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nEven though this is a clear development mistake it should be easy to detect by a Quarkus BuildStep  and provide a better error message. Query the Jandex index for embedded fields a check corresponding types for missing annotation.",
